[[File:Ti,22.jpg|thumb|right|Titanium]] '''Titanium''' is a very strong [[metal]]. It's one of hundreds of [[chemical element]]s in the [[Periodic table|periodic table]] of the elements. Its [[symbol]] is ''Ti'', and it is used in making the strongest and lightest parts of modern fighter jet planes. It does not corrode, including resistance to sea water and chlorine.
