'''Praseodymium''' is a [[chemical]] [[Chemical element|element]] that has the symbol '''Pr''' on the [[periodic table]]. It has the atomic number 59 which means it has 59 [[proton]]s in an [[atom]]. It is a soft silvery [[metal]] that can be used to make yellow-green salts. It is also mixed with [[magnesium]] to produce strong metal used in aircraft engines. It was first isolated (separated from other elements) in 1885 by the [[Austrian chemist]] [[Carl Auer von Welsbach]].
