'''Curium''' is a [[chemical element]]. It is a [[radioactive]] [[metal]]. It has the chemical symbol '''Cm'''. It has the [[atomic number]] 96. In chemistry it is placed in a group of metal elements named the [[actinides]]. Curium is a [[transuranic element]]. It is a [[radioactive]] element that does not exist in nature. Curium has to be made. Curium has a silver color. Curium is made by [[bombardment|bombarding]] a [[plutonium]] [[wikt:target|target]] with [[alpha particle]]s ([[helium]] [[ion]]s). Curium was named after [[Maria Sklodowska-Curie|Marie Curie]] and her husband [[Pierre Curie|Pierre]]. {{chem-stub}} {{Periodic Table}} [[Category:Actinides]] [[Category:Chemical elements]]
